.TH "acpi_dma_controller_register" 9 "acpi_dma_controller_register" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
acpi_dma_controller_register \- Register a DMA controller to ACPI DMA helpers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" acpi_dma_controller_register
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct dma_chan *(*acpi_dma_xlate) (struct acpi_dma_spec *, struct acpi_dma *) "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
struct device of DMA controller
.IP "acpi_dma_xlate" 12
translation function which converts a dma specifier
into a dma_chan structure
.IP "data" 12
pointer to controller specific data to be used by
translation function
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocated memory should be freed with appropriate \fBacpi_dma_controller_free\fP
call.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success or appropriate errno value on error.
